	<text>
		<body>
			<div type="entry">
				<pb facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary76.jpg"/>
				<dateline><date when="1862-06-09">Monday 9th</date></dateline>
				<p>The day was <name type="weather">dark</name> and lowering, and in the evening set
					in <name type="weather">rain</name> and <name type="weather">rained</name> all
					the night. We had a <orgName type="military">brigade</orgName> drill this
					afternoon at 4 o’clock down near the <orgName type="military">21 Mass</orgName>
					camp. The <orgName type="military">1st brigade</orgName> were drilling there
					too, and <persName key="Reno" type="general">Gen Reno</persName> was looking on
					&amp; reviewed us afterwards. Just after dinner <persName key="Lynch"
						type="general">Lynch</persName>
					<persName key="Hassenplug" type="captain">Hassenplug</persName> &amp; I went
					over to a <placeName key="plantation">plantation</placeName> across the creek
					for <name key="food"><objectName>honey</objectName></name> &amp; <name
						key="food"><objectName>mutton</objectName></name>. It was fun to see the
					n---- destroying the “<objectName type="equipment">guns</objectName>” — a bunch
					of <objectName type="nature">bees</objectName> got in their <objectName
						type="equipment">wool</objectName>. This <placeName type="plantation"
						>plantation</placeName> is immense and poverty stricken. We got a large
						<objectName type="readable">mail</objectName>. </p>
			</div>
		</body>
	</text>
